title.narrative: Integrated Maternal, Neonatal, Child Health and Nutrition/Family Planning Regional Project in Luzon (LuzonHealth)

description.narrative: (Philippines): The LuzonHealth Project will support the scale-up and institutionalization of Department of Health (DOH)-led high-impact practices to reduce maternal and infant deaths, and meet the demand for family planning services. It will focus in geographic areas with high unmet need for family planning and high teenage pregnancy rates. It will help accelerate the implementation of the Philippines' Executive Order on reducing the unmet need for family planning services, and institutionalize existing technical initiatives. USAID will use FY 2017 funds to bolster local partners' capacity to institutionalize good practices such as intensifying demand and outreach for family planning services, strengthening service delivery networks and family planning in hospitals, enhancing health providers' skills, expanding PhilHealth accreditation, strengthening the reporting system, conducting supportive supervision, and regularly conducting data quality checks.
